kers%20is%20that%20changing%20jobs%20is%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20normal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20leaving%20companies%2C%20whether%20it's%20voluntarily%20or%20involuntarily%2C%20and%20are%20looking%20to%20do%20something%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Morgan%2C%20who%20is%20the%20talent%20firm's%20president%20of%20career%20transition%20and%20mobility%2C%20and%20leadership%20development%20and%20coaching.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhether%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-after-layoff-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyou%20were%20laid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20fired%2C%20or%20chose%20to%20quit%2C%20you%20should%20approach%20the%20aftermath%20in%20pretty%20much%20the%20same%20way%2C%20experts%20say.%20The%20way%20your%20last%20job%20ended%20doesn't%20have%20to%20define%20your%20career%20%E2%80%94%20or%20derail%20your%20chances%20of%20landing%20a%20new%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20three%20job%20coaches%20and%20a%20labor%20attorney%20about%20the%20best%20steps%20to%20take%20after%20being%20fired%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d5e112c8-575f-4338-b0aa-c6b1daf00a92%5C%22%3EDon't%20act%20in%20the%20moment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20fired%20often%20comes%20with%20strong%20emotions%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20let%20them%20get%20the%20best%20of%20you%20in%20your%20initial%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-you-should-quit-job-right-future-employers-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAlan%20Stein%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20career%20service%20Kadima%20Careers%2C%20has%20been%20let%20go%20a%20handful%20of%20times%2C%20some%20of%20which%20he%20said%20he%20handled%20poorly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20fired%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20I've%20said%20some%20stupid%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Stein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStein%20said%20that%20his%20general%20advice%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bleave%20on%20good%20terms%2C%20as%20pissed%20as%20you%20might%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20burn%20the%20bridges%2C%26quot%3B%20Stein%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20industry%20is%20too%20small%2C%20and%20karma%20is%20real%2C%20so%20don't%20let%20your%20emotions%20get%20the%20worst%20of%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENatalie%20Lemons%2C%20an%20executive%20search%20and%20career%20transition%20advisor%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20people%20should%20take%20time%20to%20review%20documentation%20and%20understand%20severance%20agreements%2C%20especially%20if%20they're%20in%20an%20emotional%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2206d8ebc2-cde4-408f-89bb-dc935fc95f7d%5C%22%3ETake%20time%20to%20process%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20too%20much%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20starting%20your%20next%20search%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20process%20the%20job%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20times%2C%20whether%20it's%20a%20layoff%20or%20firing%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20go%20through%20almost%20the%20five%20stages%20of%20grief%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stacey%20Perkins%2C%20associate%20principal%20and%20career%20and%20leadership%20coach%20at%20Korn%20Ferry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20gotten%20fired%2C%20Perkins%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20reflect%20on%20what%20happened%20and%20what%20you%20can%20learn%20from%20it.%20If%20it%20was%20due%20to%20behavior%20issues%2C%20for%20example%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20take%20that%20with%20you%20to%20your%20next%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Perkins%20warns%20about%20letting%20that%20reflection%20turn%20into%20getting%20too%20hung%20up%20on%20the%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20to%20spin%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Perkins%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20surrounding%20yourself%20with%20supportive%20people%20or%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-used-chatgpt-as-career-coach-week-ai-work-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20coach%20is%20important%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStein%20said%20that%20while%20it's%20important%20to%20take%20time%20to%20process%2C%20job%20seekers%20should%20ensure%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bfinite%20amount%20of%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOtherwise%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20will%20suffer%20indefinitely%20until%20you%20start%20making%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20Stein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suggested%20allowing%20yourself%20roughly%2030%20days%20to%20process%20what%20happened.%20In%20his%20view%2C%20taking%20month%20is%20better%20than%20six%20%E2%80%94%20or%2045%20minutes%2C%20which%20he%20said%20is%20how%20long%20he%20once%20allowed%20himself%20to%20pause%20before%20starting%20his%20job%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22999479a7-1156-4d27-95a3-ae85d6fa6063%5C%22%3ECreate%20a%20job%20search%20plan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20allowing%20yourself%20to%20grieve%20the%20job%20loss%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20create%20a%20plan%2C%20similar%20to%20how%20you%20might%20if%20you%20lost%20your%20job%20in%20a%20typical%20layoff.%20That%20includes%20researching%20new%20opportunities%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexecutive-ghostwriter-shares-ways-to-brag-on-linkedin-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eupdating%20your%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-who-has-written-over-700-resumes-best-advice-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erefining%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20worth%20reaching%20out%20to%20your%20network.%20In%20an%20increasingly%20competitive%20market%20flooded%20with%20AI%20applications%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-dos-and-donts-tips-advice-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enetworking%20has%20become%20a%20key%20part%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20job-hunting%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20AI%20already%20transforming%20the%20workforce%2C%20you%20may%20also%20decide%20that%20it's%20a%20good%20opportunity%20to%20pivot.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20you%20may%20want%20to%20use%20the%20time%20to%20take%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-engineer-11-books-up-skilling-ai-job-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclasses%20or%20certifications%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0required%20to%20make%20that%20transition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f0b5352-3ab1-4bfe-9c20-18500dfdc5e6%5C%22%3EPrepare%20to%20talk%20about%20what%20happened%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20fired%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20need%20to%20wear%20a%20scarlet%20letter%20in%20future%20interviews%20%E2%80%94%20but%20you%20should%20still%20rehearse%20how%20you'll%20talk%20about%20why%20you%20left%20your%20last%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20your%20former%20employer%20won't%20share%20too%20much.%20Amy%20Epstein%20Gluck%2C%20a%20founding%20partner%20and%20chair%20of%20employment%2C%20labor%2C%20and%20benefits%20at%20Pierson%20Ferdinand%20LLP%2C%20said%20HR%20may%20be%20asked%20to%20confirm%20an%20employee's%20dates%20and%20position%2C%20and%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20whether%20they%20would%20rehire%20the%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20many%20companies%20stick%20strictly%20to%20providing%20dates%20and%20titles%2C%20since%20sharing%20negative%20information%20can%20expose%20the%20company%20to%20defamation%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20never%20know%20what%20a%20disgruntled%20former%20employee%20will%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20Gluck%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20she%20advises%20her%20clients%20not%20to%20answer%20those%20kinds%20of%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20your%20employer%20would%20reveal%20whether%20they%20would%20rehire%20you%2C%20you%20should%20still%20have%20a%20plan%20for%20how%20you'll%20talk%20about%20your%20last%20job%20in%20interviews.%20It's%20not%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20lie%2C%20but%20you%20also%20don't%20need%20to%20pro