s-friends-parks-community-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocial%20isolation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20living%20in%20a%20multigenerational%20household%20or%20an%20intergenerational%20community%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20share%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eyour%20experience%20with%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aerelman%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eerelman%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20multigenerational%20living%20may%20not%20be%20the%20norm%20these%20days%2C%20it%20once%20was.%20Before%20World%20War%20II%2C%20it%20was%20almost%20unheard%20of%20for%20older%20adults%20to%20live%20independently%20or%20receive%20care%20outside%20of%20their%20families%2C%20while%20younger%20people%20often%20wouldn't%20move%20out%20until%20they%20got%20married.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20changed%20for%20millions%20of%20American%20families%20as%20they%20lived%20farther%20apart%2C%20independent%20living%20services%20for%20seniors%20became%20more%20accessible%2C%20and%20more%20women%20joined%20the%20workforce.%20And%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fan-explosion-of-solo-agers-are-struggling-with-rising-costs-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egrowing%20number%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20older%20people%20don't%20have%20family%20to%20rely%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20more%20and%20more%20solo-agers%20who%20didn't%20have%20children%20or%20didn't%20get%20married%20or%20basically%20no%20longer%20have%20a%20relationship%20with%20their%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bob%20Kramer%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20National%20Investment%20Center%20for%20Seniors%20Housing%20and%20Care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20older%20people%20in%20particular%2C%20living%20with%20family%20or%20in%20other%20intergenerational%20arrangements%20can%20be%20life-saving%2C%20in%20part%20because%20it%20prevents%20them%20from%20growing%20isolated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bottom%20line%20for%20solo-agers%20is%20that%20they%20need%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sara%20Zeff%20Geber%2C%20a%20solo-aging%20consultant.%20%26quot%3BHowever%20creatively%20or%20traditionally%20they%20can%20work%20that%20out%2C%20that's%20what%20they're%20going%20to%20need%20if%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20be%20lonely%20and%20isolated%20and%20uncared%20for%20in%20their%20homes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntergenerational%20living%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0or%20sharing%20a%20home%20or%20community%20with%20unrelated%20people%20of%20varying%20ages%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20one%20of%20those%20creative%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20end%20of%20the%20intergenerational%20living%20spectrum%2C%20an%20older%20homeowner%20could%20have%20a%20younger%20housemate%20in%20a%20cohousing%20arrangement.%20On%20the%20other%20end%2C%20purpose-built%20intergenerational%20communities%20or%20housing%20complexes%20are%20intentionally%20designed%20for%20both%20older%20and%20younger%20residents%2C%20often%20with%20communal%20spaces%20and%20programming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gu.org%2Fapp%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2F24-HousingBlueprintReport-FINAL-WEB-v2-compressed.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20on%20intergenerational%20living%3C%2Fa%3E%20highlighted%20examples%20of%20intentional%20communities%2C%20such%20as%20One%20Flushing%20in%20Queens%2C%20New%20York.%20The%20mixed-income%20complex%20has%20231%20apartments%2C%2066%20of%20which%20are%20reserved%20for%20older%20people%2C%20and%20a%20community%20center%20that%20brings%20local%20high%20schoolers%20in%20to%20help%20older%20adults%20with%20computer%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20also%20pointed%20to%20nonprofit%20intergenerational%20housing%20communities%20in%20Oregon%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20and%20Illinois%20that%20bring%20together%20older%20adults%20and%20foster%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20costs%20remain%20a%20concern%2C%20particularly%20for%20middle-income%20people%2C%20who%20earn%20too%20much%20to%20qualify%20for%20needs-based%20government%20benefits%20but%20also%20struggle%20to%20afford%20market-rate%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20that's%20concerning%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20is%20that%20we%20really%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20options%20for%20modest-income%20folks%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robyn%20Stone%2C%20a%20senior%20vice%20president%20at%20LeadingAge%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20represents%20thousands%20of%20aging%20services%20providers%2C%20who%20contributed%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultigenerational%20or%20intergenerational%20living%20won't%20appeal%20to%20everyone.%20There's%20no%20one-size-fits-all%20housing%20solution%20for%20boomers%2C%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20or%20anyone%20in%20between%2C%20experts%20caution.%20People%20have%20vastly%20different%20needs%2C%20budgets%2C%20and%20preferences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20I%20would%20want%20to%20open%20my%20house%20to%20anybody%20if%20I%20were%20living%20alone%2C%26quot%3B%20Stone%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20think%20that%20I%20would%20want%20to%20have%20more%20of%20an%20intentional%20intergenerational%20community%20as%20I%20get%20older.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-zers-boomers-multigenerational-housing-save-rent-costs-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767692041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6952fd98832e0ef1ead6ec43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-zers-boomers-multigenerational-housing-save-rent-costs-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20cost%