of%20startups%20capitalizing%20on%20their%20quests%20for%20a%20deeper%20purpose.%20Welcome%20to%20the%20year%20of%20soft%20partying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphones-loneliness-friendship-apps-dating-fatigue-meetups-algorithms-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efriendship%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20meetup%20groups%20were%20on%20the%20rise.%20People%20were%20vibing%20at%20afternoon%20clubbing%20events%20in%20cafes%2C%20coffee-and-cold-plunge%20sessions%2C%20group%20dance%20classes%2C%20run%20clubs%2C%20and%20Zillennial-branded%20churches.%20Some%20embraced%20the%20idea%20that%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoing-offline-became-new-luxury-dating-phones-apps-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffline%20is%20the%20new%20luxury%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20hunger%20and%20the%20need%20for%20a%20deeper%20meaning%20and%20deeper%20connections%20is%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Andrew%20Roth%2C%20founder%20of%20Offline%2C%20a%20platform%20that%20helps%20people%20find%20in-person%20communities%20and%20connect%20with%20brands%20to%20co-host%20or%20be%20part%20of%20in-person%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20want%20to%20get%20out%20and%20meet%20new%20people%20are%20seeking%20new%20ways%20to%20do%20so%20beyond%20late%20nights%20at%20bars.%20Mike%20Vosters%2C%20founder%20of%20Matinee%20Social%20Club%2C%20which%20hosts%20early%20start%20and%20end%20dance%20parties%20for%20people%2030%20and%20older%20at%20iconic%20New%20York%20clubs%20like%20Joyface%20and%20Mr.%20Purple%2C%20says%20one%20of%20the%20problems%20with%20traditional%20clubbing%20is%20that%20%26quot%3Bnightlife%20in%20general%20is%20marketed%20in%20a%20very%20shallow%20way.%26quot%3B%20Long%20lines%2C%20late%20nights%2C%20bottle%20service%2C%20and%20the%20need%20to%20have%20the%20right%20look%20create%20an%20air%20of%20exclusivity%2C%20but%20also%20intimidate%20people.%20For%20the%20over%2030%20crowd%2C%20knowing%20that%20they%20can%20buy%20a%20ticket%20and%20dance%20among%20their%20peers%20and%20be%20home%20early%20is%20a%20shift%20that%20makes%20it%20more%20inclusive%2C%20and%20Matinee%20now%20hosts%20about%20three%20events%20each%20weekend%20in%20the%20city.%20%26quot%3BNightlife's%20not%20dead%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Vosters%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20think%20that%20nightlife%20needs%20to%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaura%20Baginski%20runs%20a%20similar%20venture%2C%20Earlybirds%20Club%2C%20a%20dance%20party%20that%20runs%20from%206%20to%2010%20p.m.%20and%20generally%20attracts%20women%2C%20queer%2C%20trans%2C%20and%20non-binary%20people%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2035%20and%2055.%20Most%20events%20across%20the%20country%20throughout%20January%20have%20already%20sold%20out.%20The%20early%20start%20and%20stop%20not%20only%20means%20less%20drinking%20and%20a%20full%20eight%20hours%20of%20sleep%2C%20it's%20also%20designed%20to%20be%20a%20safe%20space%20to%20meet%20new%20people%2C%20Baginski%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BGoing%20alone%20doesn't%20feel%20strange%2C%20everyone%20is%20very%20open%2C%26quot%3B%20Baginski%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20something%20different%20about%20dancing%20that%20really%20releases%20some%20tension%20and%20stress%20and%20allows%20you%20to%20connect%20with%20people%20in%20a%20different%20way%20than%20just%20sitting%20at%20a%20table%20and%20talking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESweatpals%2C%20an%20app%20that%20lets%20people%20find%20workouts%20and%20connect%20with%20their%20fellow%20gym%20buffs%2C%20is%20also%20capitalizing%20on%20the%20rising%20drives%20for%20both%20fitness%20and%20friendship.%20The%20app%20has%20raised%20%2416%20million%2C%20and%20connects%20people%20to%20events%20in%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20cities.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20looking%20at%20it%20as%20a%20way%20to%20date%2C%20as%20a%20way%20to%20meet%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20to%20work%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Salar%20Shahini%2C%20Sweatpals%20founder%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BBefore%20COVID%2C%20I%20think%20it%20was%20moving%20towards%20people%20just%20doing%20YouTube%20workouts.%20Now%20it's%20becoming%20the%20opposite.%20It's%20very%20community-based%2C%20social%2C%20and%20people%20are%20less%20interested%20in%20drinking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202025%2C%2022%25%20of%20American%20adults%20said%20they%20planned%20to%20participate%20in%20Dry%20January%20according%20to%20a%20Morning%20Consult%20poll%2C%20a%20new%20high.%20Gen%20Z%20already%20drinks%20less%20than%20older%20generations%20year-round.%20One%20in%20five%20adults%20under%20the%20age%20of%2035%20were%20interested%20in%20alcohol%20free%20events%2C%20according%20to%20a%202025%20report%20from%20Eventbrite.%20Companies%20like%20Sweatpals%20or%20Coffee%20and%20Chill%20(a%20cold%20plunge%20social%20club)%20are%20showcasing%20a%20new%20way%20of%20socializing%20that%20aligns%20with%20Gen%20Z's%20sober-curious%20values.%20It's%20a%20stark%20contrast%20to%20what%20some%20older%20pundits%20think%20will%20fix%20loneliness.%20Scott%20Galloway%2C%20author%20of%20the%20recent%20book%20%26quot%3BNotes%20on%20Being%20a%20Man%2C%26quot%3B%20believes%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20worst%20thing%20that's%20happened%20to%20young%20people%20is%20the%20anti-alcohol%20movement%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20recently%20told%20Bill%20Maher.%20%26quot%3BThe%20risks%20to%20your%2025-year-old%20liver%20are%20dwarfed%20by%20the%20risk%20of%20social%20isolation.%20%E2%80%A6%20Get%20out%2C%20drink%20more%2C%20and%20make%20a%20series%20of%20bad%20decisions%20that%20might%20pay%20off.%26quot%3B%20That%20advice%20fails%20to%20capture%20the%20interest%20of%20many%20Gen%20Zers.%20%26quot%3BSocial%20fitness%20is%20a%20new%20social%20currency%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brian%20Cho%2C%20cofounder%20at%20Patron%2C%20a%20venture%20capital%20firm%20that%20invested%20in%20Sweatpals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20expect%20more%20from%20their%20outings.%20There's%20Lectures%20on%20Tap%2C%20which%20brings%20college%20professors%20and%20experts%20to%20lecture%20at%20bars.%20Book%20clubs%20have%20moved%20from%20living%20rooms%20to%20bars%20and%20parties.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vogue.com%2Farticle%2Fphilosophy-club-is-hot-just-ask-these-gen-z-new-yorkers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephilosophy%20club%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20stirring%20up%20debates%20on%20objective%20truth%20and%20animal%20hierarchy%20in%20New%20York%20City%20bars.%20Andrew%20Yeung%2C%20founder%20of%20Fibe%2C%20a%20think%20tank%20and%20tech%20networking%20community%2C%20says%20he%20believes%20people%20in%20their%20mid-%20to%20late%20twenties%20are%20hungry%20for%20part%20of%20the%20college%20experience%20they%20lost%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20they%20want%20to%20go%20to%20is%20this%20whole%20new%20category%20of%20leisure%20events%20around%20pursuing%20your%20intellectual%20curiosity%20and%20learning%20new%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Yeung%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuke%20Evans%2C%20a%2033-year-old%20who%20runs%20a%20toy%20and%20game%20business%2C%20found%20he%20was%20hit%20with%20a%20new%20sense%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-loneliness-does-to-the-body-and-brain-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloneliness%3C%2Fa%3E%20upon%20relocating%20from%20outside%20of%20London%20to%20the%20city%20in%202025.%20He%20took%20an%20improv%20class%20to%20meet%20people%2C%20and%20has%20set%20a%20new%20goal%20of%20trying%20something%20new%20each%20month%20in%202026.%20He's%20eyeing%20a%20book%20club%2C%20a%20hiking%20club%2C%20and%20archery.%20The%20stigma%20around%20confessing%20that%20one%20feels%20lonely%20has%20subsided%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20thanks%20to%20all%20the%20attention%20on%20loneliness.%20When%20Evans%20put%20himself%20out%20there%20at%20improv%2C%20he%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Beveryone's%20in%20the%20same%20boat.%20Everyone%20feels%20a%20bit%20relieved%20that%2C%20oh%2C%20I'm%20not%20the%20only%20one%20who%20was%20feeling%20this%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20almost%20desperate%20to%20talk%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrigette%20Polster%2C%2031%2C%20made%20a%20commitment%20for%202026%3A%20no%20more%20dating%20apps.%20She's%20prioritizing%20going%20to%20bars%20and%20restaurants%20alone%2C%20and%20trying%20to%20meet%20people%20via%20her%20hobbies%2C%20which%20include%20horseback%20riding%2C%20flyfishing%2C%20and%20working%20out.%20She%20also%20wants%20single%20friends%2C%20so%20she%20started%20a%20Single%20Girls%20Night%20Out%20meetup.%20In%20just%20a%20month%2C%20Polster%20gained%201%2C500%20followers%20on%20the%20club's%20Instagram%20account%2C%20and%20hosted%20meetups%20in%20New%20Jersey%20and%20Florida.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20all%20start%20retraining%20ourselves%20to%20be%20social%20people%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Polster%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-adults-soft-partying-loneliness-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767690661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695c170704eda4732f2e7b94%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-adults-soft-partying-loneliness-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20earlybird%20clubbing%20to%20cold%20brew%20cold%20plunges%2C%20young%20adults%20are%20turning%20to%20soft%20partying%20to%20cure%20loneliness%20without%20burnout%20or%20hangovers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20